 This install applies to "Pierre Le Chef is ... Out To Lunch" © 1994 Mindscape

 This install requires WHDLoad to be in the path. It can be found in the
 WHDLoad package.

 The installed program requires 2.0 MB ChipMem and 1.0 MB OtherMem.
 It can be quit by pressing num '*' (key can be changed with Tooltype "QuitKey=").


 If you have problems with this installation please try and get a newer
 version of this package from the WHDLoad WWW-Page. If that doesn't help try
 some Tooltypes like NOCACHE, NOAUTOVEC, NOVBRMOVE, NOMMU, PAL or NTSC. If
 that also fails, please inform the author via the Bug-Report-Form which
 can be accessed on the WHDLoad WWW-Page or create a mantis issue directly
 at http://mantis.whdload.de

 For the full WHDLoad package, other installs and updates refer to:
	http://www.whdload.de/
 or	aminet:dev/misc/whdload#?
 and	aminet:game/patch/


 version 2.3 (01.02.06) done by JOTD:
 - added support for CD³² version with joypad emulation with keys
 - reworked install script & readme

 version 2.2 (01.03.05) done by JOTD:
 - added code to improve 2nd button detection

 version 2.1 (xx.11.02) done by JOTD:
 - RawDIC imager added (thanks Codetapper)
 - Install script rewritten
 - Small fixes on slave
 - source code included

 version 2.0 (2001) done by JOTD:
 - Converted to WHDLoad from Abaddon sources

 version 1.x (1997-1999) done by Abaddon
  - JST version only, no WHDLoad version
  - CACR code removed
  - Relocated decrunch routine in fastmem

 CD³² notes:

 joypad emulation keys:

 - SPACE: blue button
 - CTRL: red button
 - ALT: green button
 - P: pause button

 With a 1-button joystick, you have to use CTRL key to jump

 Game still works with a 2-button joystick and with a joypad
